  "prompt": "How do I clone a hard drive?",
  "response": "To clone a hard drive, you can follow these general steps:\n\n1. Software Method:\n- Use disk cloning software like:\n  - Clonezilla (free)\n  - EaseUS Todo Backup\n  - Acronis True Image\n  - macOS Time Machine (for Mac users)\n\n2. Basic Steps:\n- Connect the destination drive (new drive)\n- Install cloning software\n- Select source drive\n- Select destination drive\n- Start cloning process\n- Verify the clone is successful\n\n3. Hardware Method:\n- Use a hard drive duplicator/cloner device\n- Connect both drives\n- Follow device instructions\n- Press clone button\n\n4. Additional Tips:\n- Ensure destination drive is same size or larger\n- Back up important data before cloning\n- Use compatible drives (SATA, etc.)\n- Shutdown computer during process\n- Verify clone after completion\n\n5. For Windows:\n- Use built-in Windows Backup\n- Third-party software like Macrium Reflect\n- Disk Management tools\n\n6. For Mac:\n- Use Disk Utility\n- Time Machine\n- Third-party cloning software\n\nSpecific steps might vary depending on your specific hardware and software.",
